{"TopicId":194581,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Etiquette and input sanitation","CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-09T02:25:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-09T02:25:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi everyone,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve gotten a request for my mod \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179207-18x-19x-kerbal-changelog-v121-3720/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbal Changelog\u003C/a\u003E to add a button that will automatically take the user to a mod developer\u0027s website/forum page/ect as an easy way for the user to interact with the mod\u0027s userbase. In order to do this, I am going to utilize the method Application.OpenUrl, provided by Unity. They also give the warning that input needs to be sanitized before being passed in to prevent malicious URLs from being opened, to keep the users safe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI developed some code to \u0022Validate\u0022 the URLs that are given by the mod authors, and I\u0027d just like to have a sanity check before releasing something potentially dangerous to the wider KSP community.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-c prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\t\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Ebool\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EValidateWebsite\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Estring url\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tstring\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[]\u003C/span\u003